Description: Ring base of East Greek grey ware pottery vessel, possibly a krater; tall ring foot with a preominent central cone on its underside; dark grey fabric core sandwiched between dull grey margins and light grey surface with some mica and limestone inclusions; very worn dark grey polished slip on upper surface, less fine on other surfaces; inscription on upper surface.
Curator's comments: A curious piece; the orientation given here is not assured.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 457)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.075)
